## Security & Data Integrity Analysis
* **Encrypted Transmission:** Data sent to ThingSpeak uses HTTPS, ensuring transport layer security for the telemetry stream.
* **Checksum Validation:** The system incorporates DHT22 checksum verification before transmission. Invalid packets are discarded at the gateway level, preventing the injection of malformed data into the cloud database.
* **Resilience Protocol:** Implemented retry logic with exponential backoff to handle temporary signal degradation without crashing the transmission thread.
